# Issue 2 (Database Schema Migration)

Hibernate tries:

```sql
alter table epaylite_bridge_key_config
add merchant_code varchar2(255) not null
```

Oracle returns

```text
ORA-01758
table must be empty to add mandatory (NOT NULL) column
```

because the table already contains data.

### Correct approach

Instead of

```sql
ADD merchant_code VARCHAR2(255) NOT NULL;
```

do

```sql
ALTER TABLE epaylite_bridge_key_config
ADD merchant_code VARCHAR2(255);

UPDATE epaylite_bridge_key_config
SET merchant_code='DEFAULT';

ALTER TABLE epaylite_bridge_key_config
MODIFY merchant_code NOT NULL;
```

This is a database migration issue. Hibernate cannot perform this automatically on a populated Oracle table. 

---

# Issue 3 (Oracle CLOB Conversion)

Hibernate executes

```sql
alter table epaylite_mis_ws_tracking
modify request clob
```

Oracle returns

```
ORA-22858
invalid alteration of datatype
```

Oracle **does not allow** directly changing many existing datatypes to `CLOB`.

Normally you must:

```sql
ALTER TABLE ...
ADD request_new CLOB;

UPDATE ...
SET request_new=request;

ALTER TABLE ...
DROP COLUMN request;

ALTER TABLE ...
RENAME COLUMN request_new TO request;
```

or use a proper migration tool such as Flyway/Liquibase.

Again, this warning is **not what crashes your application**. 

